INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('073bbbd7-2e2b-4d5d-87cf-f9d3d00b5601', 'Chevron Corporation', 'Increasing fuel/oil prices; Increasing natural gas market; Capital investments in sector; CSR activities; To reposition itself as energy company', 'Chevron manages its investments in subsidiaries and affiliates, and provides administrative, financial, management and technology support to the United States and international subsidiaries that engage in integrated energy and chemicals operations. The Company operates through two business segments: Upstream and Downstream. Upstream operations consist primarily of exploring for, developing and producing crude oil and natural gas; liquefaction, transportation and regasification associated with liquefied natural gas; transporting crude oil by international oil export pipelines; processing, transporting, storage and marketing of natural gas, and a gas-to-liquids plant. Downstream operations consist primarily of refining of crude oil into petroleum products; marketing of crude oil and refined products; transporting of crude oil and refined products, and manufacturing and marketing of commodity petrochemicals.  Chevron Corp was founded in 1879 and is headquartered in San Ramon, California.', 'Financial stability; Global market presence; Big Global Brand', 'Government regulations; High Competition; Fuel Cell and Electric Automobiles', 'CVX', 'Cost of environmental hazards; Declining products and reserves; Legal issues');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('16494973-5db2-4b26-95a2-2dcc16de3fae', 'The Home Depot, Inc.', 'Diversifying product portfolio and catering to more customer needs; The Home Depot exclusively carries several major brands; Global expansion to other countries can help boost business for the company; Acquisition of smaller companies can help Home Depot increase sales', 'The Home Depot, Inc. (The Home Depot) is a home improvement retailer. The Company sells an assortment of building materials, home improvement products, and lawn and garden products, and provides various services. The Home Depot stores serves three primary customer groups: DIY customers, do-it-for-me (DIFM) customers and professional customers. Its DIY customers are home owners purchasing products and completing their own projects and installations. The Company assists these customers with specific product and installation questions both in its stores and through online resources and other media designed to provide product and project knowledge. Its DIFM customers are home owners purchasing materials themselves and hiring third parties to complete the project or installation. Professional Customers are primarily professional renovators, general contractors, repairmen, installers, small business owners, tradesmen. The Home Depot, Inc. was founded in 1978 and is based in Atlanta, Georgia.', 'Home Depot operates in more than 2000+ locations; The companies financial strength can be seen from its NYSE and S&P 500 index; Home Depot is one of the largest home improvement retailers in the United States; More than 400,000 people are employed with the organization; Strong financial position and growing opportunities for the company; Home Depot has a high brand recall as it is a leading market player; The company has been involved with several sponsorships in sports, political and entertainment events; The online brand of Home Depot has also been able to engage users in the USA; Out the US, it has stores in Canada, UK, China ', 'Competition within industry can affect Home Depot''s business;  Bargain power of buyer is higher and brand switching can cost loyal customers; Government policies and taxation can affect business margins', 'HD', 'Home Depot is primarily dependent on US market and has limited global presence; Intense competition means limited market share growth');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('195a7eea-e96b-4203-b4b4-db8391612cad', 'PepsiCo, Inc.', 'Pepsi should increase growth in developing countries and capture their market; Increase its product portfolio by acquisition of other brands;  Pepsico can expand the Yum! Brands eatery in untapped countries and regions like tier 2 cities; To improve its brand image by involving in more CSR activities to benefit the locals', 'PepsiCo operates as a food and beverage company worldwide. It offers branded dips, cheese-flavored snacks, and tortillas, as well as corn, potato, and tortilla chips; cereals, rice, pasta, mixes and syrups, granola bars, oat squares, oatmeal, rice cakes, simply granola; beverage concentrates, fountain syrups; ready-to-drink tea, coffee, and juices; and dairy products. PepsiCo butts heads with its eternal rival The Coca-Cola Company for the title of world''s biggest soft drinks maker. PepsiCo''s beverage brands include Pepsi, Mountain Dew, Tropicana, Gatorade, and Aquafina water. The company also owns Frito-Lay, the world''s #1 snack maker with offerings such as Lay''s, Ruffles, Doritos, and Cheetos. The Quaker Foods unit makes breakfast cereals (Quaker oatmeal, Life), Rice-A-Roni, and Near East side dishes. Pepsi products are available in 200+ countries, although the US accounts for nearly 60% of total sales. The company was founded in 1898 and is headquartered in Purchase, New York.', 'Pepsi is one of the most popular and globally recognised brands in foods and beverages; One of the most diversified product portfolio; Popular subsidiary brands like Frito Lay, Gatorade, Pepsi, Quaker, Tropicana, Yum! Brands, etc.; Pepsico has Global reach with presence in over 200 countries;  An employee strength of around 300,000 people; CSR through PepsiCo Foundation, which works in the sector of education, health, water conservation, education etc.;  Pepsi Refresh Project that funds new ideas or ventures that have the potential to benefit the society; Strong and efficient supply chain network, ensuring that all the products are available even in the most remote places; One of Pepsi''s strengths is excellent branding and advertising with global celebrity as brand ambassadors; Tie-ups, sponsorships with global sports events, music concerts, etc has been a stronghold of PepsiCo', 'Health consciousness amongst people can take a toll on its aerated drinks and snacks food markets; Compliance with different government regulations and norms in different countries; Inflation, economic slowdown and instability causes decline in the purchasing power of consumers; Strong competition from other brands in each segment of its operation can be a threat for Pepsico', 'PEP', 'Strong competition in the aerated drinks segment from Coca Cola means high brand switching; Cases against products have been blown out of proportion, thereby affecting brand image');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('1dfb4ac0-44fc-4e52-9f5f-f3f01d5d8a0c', 'Honeywell International Inc.', 'Positive outlook for global aerospace and defense sector; Growth through tie-ups and acquisitions, especially in the emerging economies like India, China, Brazil etc can boost international market share; Accelerating US turbocharged engine segment', 'Honeywell International Inc. is a technology and manufacturing company. The Company operates through four segments: Aerospace, Home and Building Technologies, Performance Materials and Technologies, and Safety and Productivity Solutions. The Company''s Aerospace segment supplies products, software and services for aircraft and vehicles. The Home and Building Technologies segment provides products, software, solutions and technologies that help owners of homes stay connected and in control of their comfort, security and energy use. The Performance Materials and Technologies segment is engaged in developing and manufacturing materials, process technologies and automation solutions. The Safety and Productivity Solutions segment is engaged in providing products, software and connected solutions to customers that manage productivity, workplace safety and asset performance.Honeywell International Inc. was incorporated in 1985 and is headquartered in Charlotte, North Carolina.', 'One of the largest American conglomerates; Employees over 130,000 people as a part of its work force; The company has its business in aerospace, engineering services, consumer products etc.; Mergers and acquisitions have consolidated the position of the company and made it one of the strongest companies in US; Sub-brands like turbo chargers and thermostats are popular through retail outlets; Strong expenditure on research and development is a good way to keep a strong market position', 'Strict govt policies and environmental regulation affect operations; Economic fluctuations and currency devaluations affect the financial performance as it is an international company; Heavy dependence on few suppliers', 'HON', 'Allegations that the company didn''t pay taxes hurt the brand image; Production of weapons in the past has also brought bad name to the company');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('2b780494-c51b-4229-8959-3c5e5c8d4ee7', 'McDonald''s Corporation', 'McDonalds can improve on the existing home delivery service; Get more innovative products for the vegetarian market in countries like India; McD centure into newer markan vets and open more locations', 'McDonald''s Corporation operates and franchises McDonald''s restaurants. The Company''s restaurants serve a locally relevant menu of food and drinks sold at various price points in over 100 countries. The U.S. segment focuses on offering a platform for authentic ingredients that allows customers to customize their sandwiches. Its High Growth Markets segment includes its operations in markets, such as China, Italy, Korea, Poland, Russia, Spain, Switzerland, the Netherlands and related markets. The International Lead markets segment includes the Company''s operations in various markets, such as Australia, Canada, France, Germany, the United Kingdom and related markets. The Foundational markets and Corporate segment is engaged in operating restaurants and increasing convenience to customers, including through drive-thru and delivery. As of December 31, 2019, the company operated 38,695 restaurants. McDonald''s Corporation was founded in 1940 and is based in Chicago, Illinois.', 'McDonalds is a hugely popular brand name and high brand loyalty; Variety of products offered by McDonalds including burgers, wraps, nuggets etc; Hygenic food preparation and quick service is provided to the customers; McDrive Drive-in service for motorists and car owners is an extremely innovative way of conducting fast food business; McDonalds has excellent advertising and marketing which makes it a top of the mind brand; Happy meal offered by McD is great attracting children especially with the toys; McDonalds is present across the world at more than 35000+ locations in more than 100 countries; More than 1.5 million are working with the company, including the franchisees; McCafe opened by McDonalds offers beverages accompany the food; The brand has been actively involved in sponsorships of global events; McDonalds has revolutionized the market with local products like Mc Aloo Tikki for India, Mc Arabia for Middle eastern countries etc', 'Threat from other eating joints/restaurants, which can reduce McDonalds'' market share; Health conscious people avoiding fast food; Being a global brand, the operations of McDonalds can be affected by recession, fluctuating economies etc; Constant vigilance from food regulatory bodies can affect business operations', 'MCD', 'High fat and high calorie food claimed to be not good for health conscious people; McDonalds has often been invovled in lawsuits regarding environment, animal rights etc');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('3045726d-bb2e-44b5-8dcc-edc262441a43', 'Target Corporation', 'Disposable income is increasing of the customers hence high purchasing power; Tapping the international market specially emerging economies can help boost business for Target retail;  Acquisition of smaller retail chains to increase business; More visibility through advertising and customer focused services', 'Target is a general merchandise retailer selling products through its stores and digital channels. Its general merchandise stores offer an edited food assortment, including perishables, dry grocery, dairy and frozen items. Its digital channels include a range of general merchandise, including a range of items found in its stores, along with an assortment, such as additional sizes and colors sold only online. Its exclusive brands include C9 by Champion, Hand Made Modern, Mossimo, DENIZEN from Levi''s, Nate Berkus for Target, Fieldcrest, Kid Made Modern, Genuine Kids from OshKosh and Liz Lange for Target. As of January 28, 2017, the Company had 1,802 stores across the United States, including 1,535 owned stores, 107 leased stores and 160 owned buildings on leased land. Target Corporation was founded in 1902 and is headquartered in Minneapolis, Minnesota.', 'Target Corporatation has more than 300,000 employees; Revenue performance is good which is backed by a strong financial position; Target retail stores are recipient of several award and recognition; Only national retailer employing a Garment Hanger reuse program; Target retail brand has approximately 1800 stores; Sponsorship of major events and sporting events has enhanced it brand visibility; It offers a wide variety of products which include health, clothing, food, toys, pet care etc', 'Huge competition from other international retail chains can affect Target''s margins; Increase raw material prices can lead to higher manufacturing costs; Increasing competition and changing economic scenarios', 'TGT', 'Past legal cases have affected the brand image of Target group at times; Despite being a strong brand, it hasn’t penetrated in to the international markets');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('34b07f69-4a95-4002-b9b6-b4de07ca21de', 'Apple Inc.', 'Apple can move into other computer or media product spaces that are not served well; Strategic alliance and innovations in technologies; People With increase in demand of Online Products people want more online music and content and Apple is tapping this market by bringing innovative products, so it can lead the market; Apple can enter gaming console market to compete with PS4 and Xbox One', 'Apple designs, manufactures and markets mobile communication and media devices, personal computers and portable digital music players. The Company sells a range of related software, services, accessories, networking solutions, third-party digital content and applications. The Company''s segments include the Americas, Europe, Greater China, Japan and Rest of Asia Pacific. The Americas segment includes both North and South America. The Europe segment includes European countries, India, the Middle East and Africa. The Greater China segment includes China, Hong Kong and Taiwan. The Rest of Asia Pacific segment includes Australia and the Asian countries not included in the Company''s other operating segments. Its products and services include iPhone, iPad, Mac, iPod, Apple Watch, Apple TV, iPhone OS (iOS), OS X and watchOS operating systems, iCloud, Apple Pay and a range of accessory, service and support offerings. Apple Inc. was founded in 1977 and is headquartered in Cupertino, California.', 'Apple corporation has around 100,000 employees worldwide; Large number of brand loyal customers; Apple is known for constant innovations in products and technology; Entering into new product lines ex: - Laptops to iPhones and iPads; It has good distribution network globally to make its products accessible online and stores;  The Apple iOS has given it a lead as compare to its competitors; Good advertising and branding through TVCs, print media, online ads and billboards; Strong legacy of the brand since its inception in 1976;  Apple''s brand name synonymous with the great leadership & legacy of Steve Jobs; Tim Cook has kept the innovation going after Steve Jobs and Apple continues to grow; New products like iPhone X and iPad pro have been well received by the market', 'Huge threat from competitors who are in mode of constant innovation; The rise of Android ecosystem in the mobile and tablet space; Mobile business is very dynamic and price sensitive especially when it comes to geographies like India, China, Brazil etc.', 'AAPL', 'It has less presence in B2B market, as compare to its competitors like Dell and HP. It can be seen that Apple mainly focuses on B2C so its losing large chunk of market; Apple ecosystem is considered to be more rigid when compared with other mobile ecosystems');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('3a5591be-fbc2-498c-bc8a-e3642b4b61b0', 'Loreal S.A.', 'L''Oréal can tap the growing market that ranges from the affluent, the aging and also the masses of the developed countries; Greater market share because of the numerous patents registered by the Company.', 'L''Oreal SA is a France-based cosmetics company. The Company owns a wide range of brands organized into four division: Consumer Products, L’Oreal Luxe, Professionals Products and Active Cosmetics. They include L’Oreal Paris, Maybelline New York, Garnier, Lancme, Yves Saint Laurent, Giorgio Armani, Kiehl’s, Krastase, La Roche-Posay and SkinCeuticals, among others. It offers a wide range of products grouped into six business segments: Skincare, Makeup, Haircare, Hair Coloring, Fragrances and Other. Skincare offering includes facial skincare, face cleaners, body care and sun protection products. The Company owns stores and ecommerce websites. It is active globally. It sells its products through distribution channels, such as hair salons, mass-market retail channels, perfumeries, department stores, pharmacies, drugstores, medispas, branded retail, travel retail, and e-commerce. The company was founded in 1909 and is headquartered in Clichy, France.', 'Continuing research and innovation in the interest of beauty which assures that the L’Oreal Cosmetics offers the best to their consumers.; L''Oréal is a leader in the growing cosmetics industry despite the competition in the market.; High-end advertising which adapts to the culture of target audience; L''Oréal has over 60,000 employees globally; Apart from hair colour, skin care, sun protection, make-up, perfumes and hair care, the company is active in the dermatological and pharmaceutical fields and is the top nanotechnology patent-holder in the United States; L’Oréal has operations in over 130 countries and over 4o manufacturing plants', 'Growing competition within the field of cosmetic brands; Economic downturn that is quite evident in other countries; L’Oreal Group may be producing the best of its line, people may find that their products are not of their basic needs and would skip buying L’Oreal products.', 'OREP', 'Decentralized organizational structure. Due to the many subdivisions of the Company, there is also the difficulty in the control of L’Oreal; Stiff competition from other leading cosmetic established brands');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('5653eea6-ecd3-4946-bfbb-f7d43a09fb77', 'The Wendy''s Company', 'Global expansion; Introduce the breakfast menu in all locations after revising the menu; Acquisition of smaller restaurants', 'The Wendy''s Company is the parent company of subsidiary holding company Wendy''s Restaurants, LLC (Wendy''s Restaurants). Wendy''s Restaurants is the parent company of Wendy''s International, LLC (Wendy''s), which is the owner and franchisor of the Wendy''s restaurant system in the United States. Wendy''s is a restaurant company specializing in the hamburger sandwich segment. Wendy''s is engaged in the business of operating, developing and franchising a system of restaurants serving food. The Company operated approximately 6,080 Wendy''s restaurants in operation in North America, as of January 1, 2017. Of these restaurants, 330 were operated by the Company and 5,768 by a total of 376 franchisees, as of January 1, 2017. In addition, as of January 1, 2017, there were 439 franchised Wendy''s restaurants in operation in 29 countries and territories other than North America. The Wendy''s Company was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Dublin, Ohio.', 'More than 40 years of experience in the fast food industry; Global presence with restaurants in around 30 countries; Third largest burger chain with around 6650 locations; Employee strength of 46000; Globally recognized brand; Stong supply chain network; Popular for its taste and use of fresh beef instead of frozen; Financial stability; Effective marketing and advertising', 'Tough competition from McDonalds and Burger king; Increase in price of raw materials; People are getting conscious about their health and avoiding unhealthy fast food; Diseases like obesity resulting from fast food consumption', 'WEN', 'Fast food perceived as unhealthy; Operation of franchisees is difficult to manage; Less number of locations as compared to its competitors globally');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('6763809e-2b4c-4c80-afd9-887d0b98489e', 'Macy''s, Inc.', 'Promoting important environmental causes; Macys can provide unconventional goods to customers and can diversify its product offerings; Company can focus organic and inorganic growth abroad', 'Macy''s, Inc. is an omnichannel retail company operating stores, Websites and mobile applications under various brands, such as Macy''s, Bloomingdale''s and Bluemercury. The Company sells a range of merchandise, including apparel and accessories (men''s, women''s and children''s), cosmetics, home furnishings and other consumer goods. Its subsidiaries provide various support functions to its retail operations. Its bank subsidiary, FDS Bank, provides credit processing, certain collections, customer service and credit marketing services in respect of all credit card accounts that are owned either by Department Stores National Bank (DSNB), which is a subsidiary of Citibank N.A., or FDS Bank. The private label brands offered by the Company include Alfani, American Rag, Aqua, Bar III, Belgique, Charter Club, Club Room, Epic Threads, first impressions, Greg Norman for Tasso Elba, Holiday Lane, Home Design, Hotel Collection. Macy''s, Inc. was founded in 1830 and is based in New York, New York.', 'Macys operates more than 600 stores in the United States; Macys has a large portfolio of private brands as well as other brands; Diversity of its merchandise includes clothing, footwear, furniture, jewelery etc; Macys exports goods and has shipment done to over 100 countries; It is a popular brand with a good recall and quality service; Macys has a strong workforce of over 150,000 employees;  Acquisition of companies has strengthened its market position;  Apart from USA, Macys has its operations in Guam & Puerto Rico', 'Increasing competition from bigger retail chains can disrupt its business; Customers using ecommerce platforms can reduce the business of Macys; Unfavorable economic conditions and government policies can affect business operations', 'M', 'Limited global awareness of Macys as compared to industry leaders;  Market share growth is less owing to intense competition');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('8c1f9b2e-e7e6-4c15-8a1a-4ec428096efc', 'ABB Ltd', 'Government  initiatives  in the infrastructure space will  augment  overall demand  for power industry; It is financially strong with huge cash flows which will help in acquisitions, buybacks and dividends; Increase in demand for smart grids increase demand for any companies that manufacture, supply or build smart grid infrastructure; Additional regulation will increase the demand for companies in the environmental services industry', 'Abb Ltd is a holding company. The Company''s segments include Electrification Products, Robotics and Motion, Industrial Automation, Power Grids, and Corporate and Other. It operates through four divisions: Electrification Products, Robotics and Motion, Industrial Automation and Power Grids. It is engaged in serving customers in utilities, industry and transport and infrastructure. The Electrification Products segment manufactures and sells products and services including low and medium-voltage switchgear, breakers, switches and control products. The Robotics and Motion segment manufactures and sells motors, generators, variable speed drives and robots and robotics. The Industrial Automation segment develops and sells control and plant optimization systems, and automation products and solutions. The Power Grids segment supplies power and automation products, systems, and service and software solutions. ABB Ltd was founded in 1883 and is headquartered in Zurich, Switzerland.', 'Huge installed customer base with long term contracts; Superior brand value has helped it in cross selling and gave a lot of aftermarket sale opportunities; ABB has resources all over the world and is geographically well spread; Significant portion of its revenue is from emerging markets which have a increasing demand for infrastructure; Well known for manufacturing  consistent top quality products around the globe', 'A bad outlook of the economy will affect the cash flows and growth of the economy; Governments are under pressure for cutting down the costs, which may slow down replacement sales and put overall sales at risk', 'ABB', 'The management has a history of overpaying for acquisitions and not delivering synergies on previous deals; On the back of shortage of liquidity, the margin is not improving in the shorter term; Bad debts and Financial difficulties with customers have increased the debtor''s provisions affecting profit');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('99559d22-58bd-4b8f-a55c-9bcf67cc61fd', 'Canon Inc.', 'The brand can focus on growth of technology; High purchasing power of the people can boost the business for Canon; Tie-up with leading mobile companies with which their cameras can be integrated; Global expansion into emerging economies can boost Canon’s business', 'Canon Inc. is engaged in the development, production, sale of office equipment, imaging systems, medical systems, industrial equipment and the provision of related services. The Company operates in four business segments. The Office segment provides office multifunction machines, laser multifunction machines, laser printers, digital continuous slip printers, digital cut sheet planters, wide format printers, document solutions. The Imaging System segment''s products include lens-interchangeable digital cameras, compact digital cameras, digital video cameras, digital cinema cameras. The Industrial Equipment and Others segment provides semiconductor exposure devices, vacuum thin film forming devices, die bonders, micromotors, network cameras, handy terminals and others. The Medical System segment provides digital radiography, X-ray diagnostic equipment, ultrasound diagnostic equipment and others. Canon Inc. was founded in 1933 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.', 'Canon is one of the leading electronics brand in the world; Canon’s wide portfolio includes digital cameras, DSLR’s, camcorders, photocopiers, printers; The company has over 180,000+ employees; The brand is present on the Tokyo Stock Exchange and also NYSE; Canon focuses on advertising through TVCs, print ads, online ads and billboards; Some of its leading digital camera brands are Canon PowerShot, Canon Digital IXUS, Canon EOS etc; It has been recognized as one of the leading environmental friendly companies in the world; Sponsorship has been done by Canon is football, motorsport etc; The company also indulges in CSR activities', 'High competition can decline Canon’s market share; Being a global brand, economic crisis and currency fluctuations affect margins; Counterfeit goods - a major threat to manufacturers of branded electronics like Canon; Availability of cheaper technology in local markets', 'CAJ', 'Intense competition means limited market share growth for Canon; Fake replicas & imitation products causes loss and hurts the brand image');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('af035162-ec04-4322-9c3f-4c3edebf51cd', 'BP PLC', 'Increasing fuel/oil prices; Increasing natural gas market; More oil well discoveries; Expand export market; Investment in alternate business', 'BP p.l.c. is engaged in the global energy business with operations in Europe, North and South America, Australasia, Asia and Africa. The Company provides customers with fuel for transport, energy for heat and light, power for industry, and the petrochemicals products used to make everyday items such as paints, clothes and packaging. The Company''s segments include Upstream, Downstream, Rosneft, and Other businesses and corporate. The Upstream segment is responsible for its activities in oil and natural gas exploration, field development and production. The Downstream segment has global marketing and manufacturing operations, and include the fuels, lubricants and petrochemicals business of the Company. Rosneft is the Company''s Russian refining business that owns and operates approximately 13 refineries in Russia, and holds stakes in three refineries in Germany, one in India and one in Belarus. BP PLC was founded in 1889 and is headquartered in London, the United Kingdom.', 'One of the biggest in the energy sector; Top in market; Huge geographical reach; High quality operations; Very Strong Brand Name', 'Government regulations; High Competition; Environment Regulations; Increasing Cost of Operations', 'BP', 'Cost of environmental hazards; Decline in production; Reaching Maturity');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('b3c5f6cf-4686-43ad-bd11-0e82b2d6ab17', 'eBay Inc.', 'The markets devoid of internet are untapped by eBay; Customers reluctant in shopping online can be persuaded; Partnerships with companies for bulk selling', 'eBay Inc., is a global commerce company. The Company’s technologies and services are designed to give buyers choice and relevant inventory and enable sellers worldwide to offer their inventory for sale, virtually anytime and anywhere. Its multi-screen approach offers downloadable, applications for iPhone operating system (iOS) and android mobile devices that allow access to some of its websites and vertical shopping experiences. The Company’s platforms are accessible through a traditional online experience, mobile devices and its application programming interfaces (APIs). Its segments include Marketplace and Classifieds. Marketplace includes its online marketplace, its localized counterparts, and the eBay suite of mobile application. Classifieds includes a collection of brands such as Mobile.de, Kijiji, Gumtree, Marktplaats, and eBay Kleinanzeigen.The company was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in San Jose, California.', 'eBay is an early market entrant with localized operations in over 30 countries; Integrated services like online ticket tracking, online money transfers etc; eBay has strong international presence providing services to a larger consumer base; A highly trusted and revered brand in the market; eBay has over 14,000 employees globally; Strong acquisitions like Skype, PayPal, Stubhub etc strengthened the brand; The company strives B2C as well as B2B businesses worldwide; eBay uses artificial intelligence & helps in data analytics based on online research & customer needs', 'Can be subjected to online frauds & security breaches which can affect the business of eBay; Risk of being involved into selling of illegal entities; Newly emerging competitive online shopping portals; Government policies & taxation can affect business margins & operations', 'EBAY', 'eBay is unable to eradicate fake or fraud sellers completely; Lesser presence in physical markets & intense competition');
INSERT INTO banksters_db.analyses (id, company, opportunities, profile, strengths, threats, ticker, weaknesses) VALUES ('b45a5ea1-debc-434f-b30b-bcec58d8e93d', '3M', 'Acquisitions to strengthen existing businesse; Automotive industry on road to recovery would mean more business; More global presence through tie-ups and diversification in businesses can lead to more growth', '3M Co is a technology company. 3M makes everything from tape to high-tech security gear. The diversified company''s products fall under four segment categories: Safety & Industrial, Transportation & Electronics, Health Care, and Consumer. 3M boasts some of the world''s most recognizable consumer brands including Post-it notes, Scotch tapes, Scotchgard fabric protectors, Scotch-Brite scouring pads, Filtrete home air filters, and ACE bandages. 3M sells products directly to users and through numerous wholesalers, retailers, distributors, and dealers worldwide. The company generates about 60% of its sales outside the US. 3M was founded by Henry S. Bryan, Hermon W. Cable, John Dwan, William A. McGonagle and J. Danley Budd in 1902 as a small mining venture in Northern Minnesota called Minnesota Mining and Manufacturing Company.', 'Strong research and development capability with over 80,000 employees worldwide; Diversified business with over 55000 products in its portfolio; It has operations in over 65 countries and commands a strong brand name; Robust cash position and financially improving performance over the years; Its product reach through retailers and distributors is in nearly 200 countries; CSR activities for environmental benefits is a good way to enhance market position', 'Unfriendly environmental regulations and strct govt policies can affect position; Intense competition can lead to loss of market share; Risks associated with conducting business outside the US', 'MMM', 'Environmental issues and litigations have sometime affected the image; Being a market leader, any mistake hurts the brand image world over');